CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 1, 1953, pg. 10 reads: Berrien-Moore Wedding -Mr. and Mrs. John Moore cut their wedding cake at the charming reception which followed their wedding in Central Baptist Church recently. The Rev. Cornell E. Talley officiated.  The bride is the former Ophelia Berrien, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Fred C. Berrien; the groom is the son of Mrs. Ada Fluellen.  The bridal gown was of handsome skinner satin with billowing tulle and Chantilly face. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of wedding party with four men, including groom John Moore wearing light colored bow tie, four women, including bride Ophelia Berrien Moore wearing lace trimmed gown with square neckline, and girl, posed in Central Baptist Church
